metadata.name: Lands #50
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.  I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction) .

 Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
 Quentin Hocdé, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: flow | meditations #229
metadata.description:
"flow | meditations" is part of the live outdoor art installation - 'Computational Convergence' at India Art Fair, held from 9-12 February 2023 in New Delhi.

To flow is to expand and contract with the waves within. A tangled chaos of particles is unhindered with a deep breath and relaxation. With permission to flow, patterns emerge.

To meditate with this artwork:
- keep your eyes moving slowly, trying not to fixate on a point.
- when thoughts arise, gently let them go and return to the artwork.
- bring your awareness again, to the act of seeing moment by moment.

Flow might arise in many ways- turbulent, synchronous, circular, ephemeral, convergent, divergent, rising, waning or a mix of any of these.

[GPU-intensive, Best viewed @ 4k/full-screen. 'j' for screencap, 'v' to toggle video recording.]

metadata.name: Semplificare #110
metadata.description:
As Bruno Munari said:

“Complicare è facile, semplificare é difficile. Per complicare basta aggiungere, tutto quello che si vuole: colori, forme, azioni, decorazioni, personaggi, ambienti pieni di cose. Tutti sono capaci di complicare. Pochi sono capaci di semplificare."

Made with love, p5.js, glsl and p5.grain
Zamboni | Feb. 2023

metadata.name: A collage of collages #70
metadata.description:
Lots of eyes, lots of mouths, lots of other features. Don't know how else to describe how else it goes.

Almost all the eyes are from GAN projects, some are from CC0 searching. Everything is either GAN or CC0, no copyrighted materials used here. Specific feature or otherwise. 

The number of potentials for this is SUPER hight, I think it's 10*10*9*10*12*10*9 combinations

Hope you enjoy!
